Caledonia Mining Corporation has announced quarterly and annual gold production from the Blanket Mine in Zimbabwe for Q4 2021. All production numbers are expressed on a 100% basis and are based on the final assay at the refiners. Commenting on the announcement, Steve Curtis, Chief Executive Officer, said: “This has been an outstanding performance and a tremendous team effort. I would like to thank all our employees for their hard work in achieving this result and that we were able to exceed our revised annual production guidance. “The commissioning of the Central Shaft, record gold production, along with a continued commitment to safety, all in one year, is an outstanding achievement and testament to the quality of the Caledonia technical team. “Now that the Central Shaft is complete, the Company will also focus on other areas of its growth strategy, as we continue to evaluate investment opportunities, with a vision of becoming a multi asset gold producer.”